creator: Thomas Hood
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 9 recordings of recording of Sally Simpkin's Lament; or, John Jone's Kit-Cat-Astrophe by Thomas Hood. This was the Fortnightly Poetry project for January 4, 2015. Read in English by Ahmad Abdullah; David Lawrence; Garth Burton; Greg Giordano; Jason Mills; Larry Wilson; Leonard Wilson; MaryAnn and Maria Kasper. Thomas Hood was a British humorist and poet, born in London. ( Summary from Wikipedia ) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
